The vigil that faithful hold in churches on Christmas eve was missing.Church doors, which had remained open over many years, were put under lock and key. That was a unique Christmas. The funfair that always accompanies the day was gone. Families were hurdled in grief after the coronavirus snatched away a loved one or put them in the hospital ward. 
This has always been the day. Even for the less fortunate, it came with goodies — with the rare assurance of eating meat. If you grew up in a less fortunate family, like I did, then you know that meat is a preserve for visitors — and occasions.



